---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ContactSalesModal from "../components/ContactSalesModal.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Statement - Helpmaton">
  <Header />
  <main class="min-h-screen p-8 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-display-2 font-display text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
          Helpmaton Privacy Statement
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">Last updated: January 13, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="privacy-content prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">1. Who we are</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Helpmaton is operated by <strong>Gordon & Teixeira Lda.</strong> (Portugal) and its affiliates (including
            <strong>DjiniLabs</strong>). The company responsible for your account depends on your region and is shown on
            your checkout or invoice.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <strong>Privacy contact:</strong> <code>privacy@helpmaton.com</code>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">2. Information we collect</h2>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">2.1 Information you provide</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-4">
            <li><strong>Account information:</strong> name (optional), email address, and login identifiers.</li>
            <li><strong>Workspace data:</strong> workspace names, team/member details, permissions, and settings.</li>
            <li><strong>Agent configuration:</strong> prompts, enabled tools, integration settings, and related options.</li>
            <li><strong>Customer Content:</strong> messages, documents, uploaded files, and other content you choose to store or process via the Service.</li>
            <li><strong>Support communications:</strong> messages you send us (including emails and in-app support requests).</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <strong>Password note:</strong> Helpmaton uses <strong>passwordless “magic link” authentication</strong> for
            the web UI. We do not ask you for a password to log in and do not store plaintext passwords for that login
            flow.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">2.2 Information collected automatically</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> feature usage, requests, and performance/diagnostic data.</li>
            <li><strong>Device and network data:</strong> browser type, device identifiers, IP address, and general location derived from IP.</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies and similar technologies:</strong> used for session management, security, and analytics (where enabled).</li>
            <li><strong>Logs and error reports:</strong> to detect, prevent, and address technical issues.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">3. How we use information</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">We use information to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <li>Provide, maintain, secure, and improve the Service.</li>
            <li>Authenticate users and prevent fraud or abuse.</li>
            <li>Process payments and administer subscriptions and credits.</li>
            <li>Provide customer support and respond to requests.</li>
            <li>Monitor usage, enforce limits, and troubleshoot issues.</li>
            <li>Comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">4. AI providers, integrations, and third parties</h2>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">4.1 AI providers and model routing</h3>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Depending on your setup, we may send parts of your Customer Content (such as prompts, messages, and
            relevant context) to third-party AI providers to generate outputs.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">You may use:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-4">
            <li><strong>Bring Your Own Key (BYOK):</strong> you provide your own AI provider key (for example via OpenRouter). In that case, the provider may bill you directly under its terms.</li>
            <li><strong>Credits:</strong> you purchase credits through Helpmaton, which may cover eligible AI usage.</li>
          </ul>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">4.2 Other integrations</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            The Service can integrate with third-party services (for example: Slack/Discord, email providers, MCP
            servers, secure sign-in (OAuth) providers). When you enable an integration, data may be sent to and from that service based
            on your configuration.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            We are not responsible for third-party services’ privacy practices. Please review their privacy policies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">5. How we share information</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information. We may share information with:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <li><strong>Service providers (subprocessors)</strong> that help us operate the Service (for example hosting, analytics, error monitoring, email delivery, payments).</li>
            <li><strong>Third-party integrations</strong> you enable (as described above).</li>
            <li><strong>Legal and safety purposes:</strong> to comply with law, respond to lawful requests, protect rights and safety, investigate fraud/security incidents, and enforce our Terms.</li>
            <li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> if we are involved in a merger, acquisition, financing, reorganization, bankruptcy, or sale of assets, information may be transferred as part of that transaction.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="cookie-preferences" class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">6. Cookies and cookie preferences</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Our website uses cookies and similar technologies in three categories:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-4">
            <li><strong>Essential:</strong> required for the site to function (for example, storing your cookie consent choice).</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> help us understand how the site is used (we use PostHog, hosted in the EU).</li>
            <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> used for campaign measurement (we use Google Ads and LinkedIn Insight).</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-4">
            Your choices are stored in your browser. To change or withdraw consent, use the link in the website footer or
            the button below to reset your preferences and show the cookie consent bar again.
          </p>
          <button
            type="button"
            id="privacy-reset-cookie-preferences"
            class="rounded-lg border border-neon-cyan/40 bg-transparent px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)] transition-colors hover:bg-neon-cyan/10 hover:border-neon-cyan/60"
          >
            Change cookie preferences
          </button>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">7. Data retention</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            We keep information as long as needed to provide the Service, comply with law, resolve disputes, and enforce
            agreements.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]"><strong>Examples of retention behavior in the product:</strong></p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <li><strong>Conversation file uploads</strong> (e.g., attachments) may be stored with an automatic expiration policy (currently <strong>30 days</strong> for conversation file storage).</li>
            <li><strong>Agent memory summaries</strong> follow plan-based retention windows (for example, “working” memory is kept for limited hours and summaries for limited periods). Documents are not automatically deleted.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            You can request deletion of certain data as described in Section 10.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">8. Security</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            We use technical and organizational measures to protect information. However, no system is 100% secure, and
            we cannot guarantee absolute security.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">9. Important product privacy notes</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <li><strong>Agent tools and access:</strong> Agents can use tools that access documents, memory, external services, or third-party APIs. Enabling tools can increase the data an agent can access and process.</li>
            <li><strong>Memory search warning:</strong> Memory search can let an agent recall information across conversations. Misconfiguration may increase the risk of unintended disclosure. Only enable features you understand and have assessed for your use case.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">10. International transfers</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            We may process and store information in countries other than where you live. Where required, we use
            appropriate safeguards for cross-border transfers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">11. Your rights and choices</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">Depending on where you live, you may have rights to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <li>Access and obtain a copy of your personal data.</li>
            <li>Correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your personal data.</li>
            <li>Object to or restrict processing.</li>
            <li>Data portability.</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            To exercise rights, contact <code>privacy@helpmaton.com</code>. We may need to verify your identity and
            authority.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">12. Children's privacy</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            The Service is not intended for individuals under <strong>18</strong>. We do not knowingly collect personal
            information from children.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">13. Changes to this Privacy Statement</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            We may update this Privacy Statement from time to time. We will post the updated version and update the
            “Last updated” date.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="rounded-xl p-6 mb-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">14. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">Questions or requests:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            <li>Email: <code>privacy@helpmaton.com</code></li>
            <li>Address: Gordon & Teixeira Lda., Funchal, Madeira, Portugal</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
  <ContactSalesModal />
  <style>
    .privacy-content :global(code) {
      background: rgba(0, 245, 255, 0.1);
      color: #00f5ff;
      padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
      border-radius: 0.25rem;
      font-size: 0.9em;
    }
  </style>
  <script>
    document.getElementById('privacy-reset-cookie-preferences')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      localStorage.removeItem('helpmaton_cookie_consent');
      window.location.reload();
    });
  </script>
</Layout>
